# Episode 04 – Understanding Internal Business Automation

In this episode, I experimented with Gmail notifications.

The objective was to understand how customer-facing automation and internal business automation work together.

I tested a workflow where customer complaints could trigger an email notification. This helped me understand how businesses can automatically alert support teams when important customer issues appear.

While testing, I discovered that when Gmail becomes the final node in a chat workflow, the chat interface displays the Gmail output instead of the AI response.

Although simple, this lesson taught me an important workflow design principle.

Key Learning:
Customer responses and internal business actions should be designed separately whenever possible.
